{"ts":"2026-04-18T16:07:07Z","event":"clarify_critic","feature":"instrument-eventslog-aggregation-for-turns-and-cost-per-tier","findings":["The HIGH rating for intent clarity rests on four enumerated deliverables, but two of them (escalation frequency per error type; rate-limit incident count + concurrency reduction duration) depend on event-schema signals the source never confirms exist — the assessment itself flags this as an open research question, which is inconsistent with a HIGH rating.","The ticket silently expands DR-4's two-dimension ask (turns + cost) to four dimensions (adding escalation frequency and rate-limit incidents); the assessment never reconciles the expansion with the source's own stated motivation, so the implementer has no grounding for whether the added dimensions are load-bearing or scope creep.","The MEDIUM-leaning-LOW scope rating understates the problem: the source explicitly delegates three orthogonal design axes (format/location/ergonomics), schema coverage for 2 of 4 deliverables is unverified, and the metrics.json overlap is unresolved — this is LOW, not MEDIUM.","The HIGH requirements-alignment rating is an absence-of-evidence claim: the source does not cite requirements/pipeline.md or requirements/observability.md, does not acknowledge lifecycle/metrics.json, and does not state the relationship — 'no explicit conflict' is not equivalent to 'aligned'.","The complex complexity rating leans on downstream-coupling rationale (#088, #089, matrix recalibration depend on this) which is not a lifecycle complexity dimension; the ticket frames the work as 'a small script' so complex may be a default-bias call, not evidence-based.","The medium criticality rating under-accounts for silent-failure risk in aggregation math: bugs that produce plausible-looking-but-wrong numbers would contaminate downstream matrix recalibration decisions, which are not cheaply reversible."],"dispositions":{"apply":3,"dismiss":2,"ask":1},"applied_fixes":["Revised intent clarity HIGH -> MEDIUM: two of four enumerated deliverables rest on unverified events.log schema signals; research must verify them before they can be treated as concrete outputs.","Revised scope boundedness MEDIUM (leaning LOW) -> LOW: three orthogonal design axes delegated to implementer, schema uncertainty for 2 of 4 outputs, and unreconciled metrics.json overlap compound to LOW, not medium.","Revised requirements alignment HIGH -> 'Partial alignment': adjacent to requirements/pipeline.md §Metrics and Cost Tracking (existing lifecycle/metrics.json per-feature aggregator), but ticket source does not cite the requirements doc and does not reconcile the relationship with the existing system."],"dismissals":[{"finding_index":4,"rationale":"Complex tier is grounded in clarify.md §5 dimensions 'requires judgment calls about design trade-offs' (extend-vs-add with existing lifecycle/metrics.json) and 'introduces new patterns' (per-dispatch aggregation vs existing per-feature aggregation); the downstream-coupling rationale in the original assessment was a supporting comment, not the primary basis for the rating."},{"finding_index":5,"rationale":"Medium is defensible — aggregation tool is isolated and read-only, silent-failure risk in analysis tools is universal and mitigated by test fixtures, and clarify.md §5's 'high' default is scoped to skill/lifecycle/hook/workflow changes rather than instrumentation tooling; downstream matrix recalibration decisions have human-in-the-loop review before action, which mitigates silent-failure-to-decision risk."}],"status":"ok"}
